==English==

===Etymology===
Hebrew הָגָר (Hagar), meaning "Stranger". (Arabic هاجر; Hajar; Hebrew הָגָר "Stranger", Standard Hebrew Hagar, Tiberian Hebrew Hāḡār)

===Proper noun===
'''Hagar'''

# (Bible) Concubine of [[Abraham]], mother of [[Ishmael]].
#{{given name|female|from Hebrew|}} A female [[given name]].

